{
  "texts": [
    "LlaMa 2 outperformed the comparatively lower F 1 score of 0.66 achieved using MaterialsBERT, particularly during the extraction of bandgap, where it achieved an accuracy of 0.77.",
    "GPT-3.5 once again secured the highest F 1 scores of 0.87 and 0.85 for the Random and Similar-shot selection methods, respectively.",
    "We previously demonstrated the superior performance of MaterialsBERT compared to other existing NER models 11.",
    "The higher F 1 scores compared to the MaterialsBERT obtained in this work thus underscores the advantage of the LLMs over the existing NER models.",
    "Concerning computational efficiency and monetary costs, Materi-alsBERT emerges as the most advantageous choice (Fig. 3e)."
  ]
}